The paper discusses the development of practical protocols for verifiable computation, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The focus is on circuit evaluation, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) as well as information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the runtime of the prover, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
